</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usherekhaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shere Khaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/26/01 8:58:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC spawn in OOT</span><hr size=1> Actually this is exactly how I got my AC ring at level 45. <br>
<br>
I hated camping Sro because there were always 5 other people there and if he did pop only had a small chance of getting him. I thought stuff it I'll go to OOT, couldn't be that hard...<br>
<br>
Well it was hard and I managed to hold down the spawn for about 45 minutes (2 out of 3 spawns were cyclops). I had to give the spawns 2-3 minutes wandering time in order to med fully and it always took me a full bar if not more to take one down. I had a couple of stacks of sow potions so that was not a problem and the zone was empty so no chance of being KS'd.<br>
<br>
After 45 minutes the AC popped, how lucky was that! I only had 50% mana and meditated to 70% before I got too nervous and initiated combat so he wouldn't despawn.  I had a backup plan though. I was bound on the island and figured I could still take him down on my second life - I was quite willing to die for these boots.<br>
<br>
Anyway 60% mana took him down to only 60% health leaving me with half a bubble of mana. So began my longest solo combat I have ever done. I kited the AC round the island for 15 minutes with BoF and roots for med time. I ended up going through 2 harvests to take him down and was terrified he would despawn because it wqas taking so long. This was one of my best victories as I didn't have to resort to dying <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ultimately a level 45 wizard can do he OOT spawn but be ready for a rough time and take at least a couple of sow potions with you. Also I imagine I could have been KS'd relatively easily as an enchanter appeared soon after I got the ring and could easily have mem blurred I guess.<br>
<br>
I refrained from telling him the AC just spawned and took off to complete the quest.<br>
<br>
